helpText: !{0} tap to tap the module before the logic dive. !{0} logic 1-9 to tap the button in that position in reading order. !{0} cut 1-3 to cut wires (Three Wires). !{0} press/tap 1-6 to press a button (Colored Buttons/Punctuation Buttons/Colored Piano/Colorful Message).  Commands that are related to a selected module after a logic dive can be chained. To press the small button in Colorful Message, do !{0} message.

"!{0} press Red/Orange/Yellow/Green" to press the specified button in the command. Shorthand abbreviations are acceptable. Presses can be combined by spacing out the commands or as one word when abbreviated, I.E "!{0} press royg".
!{0} screen to toggle color blind mode. !{0} submit|sub|s 1234567890 to submit the number.
!{0} submit <ans> [Submits an answer of 'ans'] | Valid answers have only letters
!{0} yes/y [Presses the 'YES' button] | !{0} no/n [Presses the 'NO' button]
!{0} Perdita [submit the name Perdita]

!{0} KRGBCMYW [Selects colour] | !{0} 1-14 [Changes segment (in reading order) to selected colour] !{0} cb [Activates colourblind mode] | !{0} submit | !{0} next / !{0} skip [Moves to next display / Skips remaining displays (only following an incorrect submission)] | Colouring commands can be chained, separated with spaces e.g. R 1 2 G 12 13

Press a button with “!{0} A1 B2 C3 D4...”. Columns are labeled A-D from left to right, rows are labeled 1-4 from top to bottom. Commands may be voided if the module enters a generation state or a solve state. "press" is optional.
To toggle colorblind: "!{0} colorblind" To generate a new board: "!{0} regen[erate]" or "!{0} reset". You can only regenerate up to 3 times on this module! To get the number of resets this module currently used up: "!{0} resetcount"
!{0} up/down (#) [Press the up or down arrow (optionally '#' times)] | !{0} submit [Presses the LED]
Use !{0} 9/10/display to press that corresponding button. Use !{0} reset/submit to do the corresponding action. Chain using spaces.
!{0} toggle <#> [Toggles the specified LED '#' (chainable with spaces between each LED)] | !{0} submit [Presses the submit button] | !{0} colorblind [Toggles colorblind mode] | Valid LEDs are 1-3
!{0} move L F R F U [move] | !{0} walk L F R F U [walk slower] [L = left, R = right, F = forward, U = u-turn]
Use '!{0} move u d l r' to move around the grid. Use '!{0} submit' to press the goal button.
Press a button with “!{0} tl” or “!{0} 1”. Buttons are tl, tm, tr, ml, mm, mr, bl, bm, br, or numbered 1–9 in reading order. Commands can be chained but must be spaced out. "press" is optional.
!{0} hold (Starts the number cycle) | !{0} release [1-11] (Releases at the specified number (11 is blank))
!{0} hold (Starts the number cycle) | !{0} release [1-11] (Releases at the specified number (11 is blank))
Use '!{0} reset left 0 1 10101 submit' to reset the module, press the buttons, and submit. The first letter of the reset and submit commands can be used also.

"!{0} R G B C M Y K W" to select the color, "!{0} 1 2 3 4 5 6 7" to select the segments in reading order. These two commands can be chained, I.E "!{0} R 1 C 2...".
Cycle the stages with "!{0} led cycle" or "!{0} led cycle # #" for specific stages, go to a specific stage with "!{0} led #", or press the LED once with "!{0} led". Modify the cycle speed with "!{0} cyclespeed #" (0.5-9.5 seconds only) Highlight the segment's in reading order with "!{0} segments".
Submit the current setup or enter submission mode with "!{0} submit". Colorblind mode can be enabled viva "!{0} colorblind". Get each segment's color quicker with colorblind enabled by doing "!{0} colorblind fastreads".
Use '!{0} pot 3 5' to pot the balls labelled 3 and 5.
!{0} left/right (#) (slow) [Presses the left or right arrow (optionally '#' times and/or slow presses)] | !{0} send [Presses the send button] | !{0} submit [Presses the submit button]
!{0} touch [any time] | !{0} touch 1 [when last digit is 1] | !{0} touch 05 [when seconds section is 05]
Submit your answer with “!{0} submit <input>”.
Submit a response code with “!{0} submit (code)”. For example, “!{0} submit 100” for code 100.
!{0} go/start [press the GO button] | !{0} WLMN [press these letters (note: This will also press the GO button)]
Submit the answer with “!{0} submit 1234”. Clear the display with “!{0} clear”.
Submit or input a number using '!{0} <submit|input> <number>'. Cycle, clear, or submit by using '!{0} <cycle|clear|submit>'.
!{0} submit DPC INUF [submit letters to be pushed down; all other letters are brought back up] | !{0} submit! [bring all letters up and submit that]
!{0} submit 4 5 6 7 12 [submit buttons to be pushed down; all other buttons are brought back up] | !{0} submit АЯЖПШЪ [likewise] | !{0} submit! [bring all letters up and submit that]

Cycle the stats with !{0} cycle stats. Cycle the Weapons/Items with !{0} cycle items. Cycle everything with !{0} cycle all. Use weapons/Items with !{0} use potion. Use multiple items with !{0} use ticket, crystal ball, caber. (spell out the item name completely. not case sensitive)
!{0} QWERTYUI [Inputs letters] | !{0} cancel [Deletes inputs]
Press buttons using !{0} press <buttons>. Runes are specified directionally. Frequencies are specified by full name. Other buttons: redraw, submit and clear.
Type '!{0} submit <value>' OR '!{0} <value> submit'. Type '!{0} clear' to clear the screen.
Take the correct actions using !{0} [attack/defend/pass] [1-3], or !{0} [a/d/p] [1-3]. Use !{0} [left/right] to move in that direction.
Submit your answer with “!{0} press A B C D”.
Press the buttons with !{0} press 1 2 3 4 5 6. The buttons are numbered 1 to 6 in clockwise order, with 1 being at the top.
!{0} press <#> [Presses the button labeled '#'] | Valid numbers are 1-9

Use the command !{0} left/right to press the corresponding side on the module. You can use the command !{0} update to update the rule list being applied in the module (This however resets all inputs in the module)
Type '!{0} submit <letter1> <letter2>' to submit a full stage. Type '!{0} submit <letter>' to submit a single answer. The first stage must be submitted before the second.

'!{0} tap UUDDLRLR' | '!{0} hold U' | '!{0} release any' (any time) | '!{0} release on 4' (4 on either digit) | '!{0} release on not 2' (2 not present) | '!{0} release on 06 12 18' (exact number of seconds) | '!{0} reset' (return to the start)
!{0} submit 123 to submit 123. Do !{0} cycle to cycle stages (only when you have struck four times).
Submit your answer with !{0} submit poodle
Press a button with “!{0} press up”, or chain button presses together with “!{0} press up down left”. Can use the initials of the buttons in place of words (“u” instead of “up” for example).

!{0} listen [Listens to your friend's last recorded message] | !{0} dial <phone#> [Dials the specified phone number] | Valid phone numbers have 10 digits | The 10th digit will automatically be submitted at the correct time
!{0} cycle | !{0} cycle A/B/C | !{0} toggle [press each screen once] | !{0} submit 97 98 99
Use !{0} press 1-8 to press an arrow where 1 is the arrow in north north west and going clockwise.
Use '!{0} appreciate {0}' to appreciate a module.
Use '!{0} query 42' to query that number. Use '!{0} submit <topleft|topright|bottomleft|bottomright> to submit that button. You can also use <tl|tr|bl|br>.
!{0} scroll <lr> [Cycles between displays] | !{0} move <udlr> [Moves around the maze] | !{0} cb [Activates colourblind mode]| !{0} submit | !{0} reset
!{0} L/R # [Presses the left/right button # number of times.] | Valid numbers are 1-9.
Press good on 3 with !{0} press good on 3. Press bad on 2 with !{0} press bad on 2. No Omen is !{0} press no
Use '!{0} 1' to press the top-left button (buttons are numbered in reading order) | '!{0} play' to press the play button

Type '!{0} press left', '!{0} press m' or '!{0} r' to press the button in that position. Can also use numbers 1-3 instead (buttons are ordered 1, 2, 3). Type '!{0} press play' to press the play button.
Press a character using using !{0} press <character>. Characters: baba, keke, me, rock, flag and wall.

Place a bet with "!{0} bet <amount> on <location>". Bet on multiple locations with "!{0} bet <amount1> on <location1>, <amount2> on <location2>, ...". Betting locations are "player", "banker", "tie", "player pair", and "banker pair". Use "!{0} colorblind" to activate colorblind mode. Use "!{0} tilt d" to get a better view of the table limits.
Use '!{0} press 5' to press the "Push Me" button 5 times, Use '!{0} Submit' to Submit the current answer. Note: Only takes numbers 1-9
Choose the left or right hand with '!{0} left' or '!{0} right'. Switch decks with '!{0} deck <name>'. (Try 'default' or 'four-color'; there may be others.)

!{0} press <button> at <##>/<#> [Presses the specified button when the last two digits/the last digit of the bomb's timer are '##'/is '#'] | !{0} led <LED> [Presses the specified LED, where <LED> can be l=left, ml=midleft, mr=midright, or r=right] | !{0} reset [Resets all current inputs but NOT the module] | !{0} first [Pauses text cycling at first display] | Valid buttons are tl(topleft), tm(topmiddle), tr(topright), bl(bottomleft), bm(bottommiddle), or br(bottomright)

!{0} press ## [Presses the button when the seconds digits of the bomb's timer are '##'] !{0} dtap # [Double taps the button when the last seconds digit of the bomb's timer is '#'] | !{0} reset [Remove any inputs made into the module]
!{0} 1-16 [Presses button in that position in reading order] | !{0} reset [Presses reset button]

To interact a given button at a specific time: "!{0} hold/tap l[eft]/m[iddle]/r[ight] at ##:##" Time format is MM:SS with MM being able to exceed 99 min.
To release a button at a specific time based on the display or bomb timer: "!{0} release display/bombtime at ##:##" To release a button based on the seconds timer: "!{0} release display/bombtime at ## ##" Multiple time stamps are acceptable when releasing the button.
To get the current time on the display: "!{0} display time" To switch between stages: "!{0} toggle/switch"
To activate colorblind mode: "!{0} colorblind" You can only activate colorblind mode or switch stages if you are NOT holding a button!

!{0} add 1 9, 2 2 [add 9 times ingredient 1, 2 times ingredient 2] | !{0} slot 1 | !{0} slot 2 | !{0} trash | !{0} iced | !{0} aged | !{0} mix 4 [mix for that many seconds] | !{0} bottled A Fedora | !{0} serve
Use '!{0} 482' to submit 482 as your answer.
Use !{0} up/down to press the corresponding arrow, !{0} submit XXXX to submit a word.

Scan the safe spots with “!{0} radar A2 B3 E5”. Mark the spots as water with “!{0} water A1 A3 B4”. Mark the spots as ships with “!{0} torpedo E3 E4”. Fill in rows or columns with water with “!{0} row 3 4” or “!{0} col B D”.

Use '!{0} submit bee horn' to submit the prefixes of the names. Use '!{0} left down' to flip the left page down. Use '!{0} submit to submit the current names. Make sure you include punctuation if there is any.
!{0} tap [tap the button] | !{0} hold [hold the button] | !{0} release 7 [release when the digit shows 7]

Submit the correct response with !{0} press blue black red. Reset the module with !{0} reset.  (Valid colors are Red, Orange, Yellow, Green, Blue, Magenta, White, blacK). Enable colorblind mode with !{0} colorblind. You can also be silly, and cause the circle to spin at random speeds/direction and fade in and out with !{0} spin
!{0} submit 01 [submits the code 01], !{0} press useless button [pressing useless button]
Use '!{0} <reset|check|submit> to reset/check the grid, or toggle submit. Use '!{0} a1 b2' to press those squares. Commands can be shortened to the first letter and chained using spaces.
Cut the wire on a specific sequence with !{0} cut red 25 26 8. (The color wire will be cut on the last number specified.)

!{0} A1 [toggle a square] | !{0} row 4 011001 [change an entire row] | !{0} col C 101001 [change an entire column] | !{0} solve 100101001011010110110100101001011010 [give a full solution] | !{0} reset
Press a button with “!{0} press 1”, where the buttons are numbered 1–7 in reading order.
!{0} 31 12 [Submits December 31st. Single digit numbers must be submitted with leading zeroes, e.g. March 5th is 05 03.]
!{0} press 2 [press button 2]
Submit the correct answer with !{0} submit 10101010.
Move to other screens using !{0} right|left|r|l|. Submit the decrypted word with !{0} submit qwertyuiopasdfghjklzxcvbnm
!{0} hold, tick, release | !{0} tap, tick, tap [specify when to hold, release, tap, or wait for a timer tick in the correct order]
Type '!{0} bet 10' to bet $10. Type '!{0} hit' to get another card and '!{0} stand'. To check for blackjack at the start, type '!{0} check'
!{0} TL, TM [top-left, top-middle, etc.]
!{0} press <coord> [Presses the button at the specified coordinate] | Valid coordinates are A1-E5
Use !{0} nwse or !{0} uldr to move North West South East. Use !{0} reset to reset back to the start.
!{0} submit <nums> [Submits the specified number sequence] | !{0} colorblind [Toggles colorblind mode] | Valid numbers are 1-3
!{0} 1;4;5;2 [Selects the block pairs '1 and 4' and '5 and 2' with 1-6 being the block's positions on the module from left to right]
Press a tile using !{0} B5. Tiles are specified by column then row.
!{0} ULLURDD [move in the specified directions] | !{0} reset
Use !{0} press ## to select the module at a certain time.

!{0} up/down/left/right [Presses the specified arrow button] | !{0} left right down up [Chain button presses] | !{0} reset [Resets the module back to the start] | Direction words can be substituted as one letter (Ex. right as r)
Move to other screens using !{0} right|left|r|l|. Submit the decrypted word with !{0} submit qwertyuiopasdfghjklzxcvbnm
Use '!{0} TL TR BL BR' (position) or '!{0} 1 2 3 4' (reading order) to press the buttons. Use '!{0} mute' to silence until another input is given.
Use “!{0} press a1 a2” to press any number of buttons in that order, using a–d for columns and 1–4 for rows.

!{0} open <menu> [Opens the specified menu, the three valid menus are 'Main', 'Destination', and 'Components'] | !{0} back [Heads back to the main menu] | !{0} destination USA #1;Delaware [Sets the destination's sector and area] | !{0} component batteries 2 [Sets the specified component of batteries, indicators, port (NO SPACES IN PORT NAMES), or manuals] | !{0} component cycleportsleft [Cycles through all ports in the 'Components' menu to the left] | !{0} tilt r [Use to see ports on the right side of the B.D.S., this command is a general TP command] | !{0} go [Submits the current configuration]
!{0} submit 8T [Submits the specified pair of characters, in this example '8' and 'T' respectively]
Press the button containing the character, who said the quote by doing “!{0} press tl”. (Locations are tl, tr, bl, br.)
Use '!{0} press 2 4' to press buttons 2 and 4. | Buttons are indexed 1-4 in reading order.
Press buttons using !{0} press <button>. Buttons can be specified in full or based on their last character.
Select parts of the diagram with !{0} a bc abc. Options are A, AB, ABC, AC, B, BC, C, O (none).
Use '!{0} submit <operator>' to submit the specified operator! Valid operators are: OR; XOR; AND; NAND; NOR.
'!{0} submit' to submit the configuration. '!{0} 5u/d/l/r' to move piece 5 (and other necessary pieces) up/left/down/right. Commands can be chained. e.g. '!{0} 5u 6l 4r 1d'
!{0} <button1> <button2> [Presses the buttons in the specified two positions] | Valid button positions are TL,TM,ML,MM,MR,BL,BM,BR
!{0} submit <boz> <set> [Submits the boozleglyph 'boz' from set 'set'] | Valid boozleglyphs are A-Z | Valid sets are 1-3
Use !{0} submit 5 to submit when the last digit of the timer is 5.
!{0} press 0123456 [position in reading order; 0 is the black button up top] | !{0} cycle [shows border colors in reading order] | !{0} colorblind
!{0} punch [Use the punch power machine] | !{0} left/right [Presses the left or right arrow] | !{0} hire [Presses the hire button] | !{0} abstain [Presses the abstain button]
!{0} cycle [show the Braille letters] | !{0} press 1 [press the first letter]
Input the answer with “!{0} (answer)”, eg: “!{0} 28” to input 28. Use “!{0} clr” to clear the input and “!{0} ok” to submit.
!{0} set <data> <input> [Sets the specified data piece 'data' to 'input'] | !{0} restore/submit [Presses the restore button] | Valid data pieces are name, home, attribute, and faction
!{0} press <X> (Presses the button with the label <X> breaks. You must specify decimals with periods.)

Use !{0} press b1 b4 g7 e7 to press the islands at the respective coordinates. Use !{0} submit to submit. Letters refer to columns and numbers refer to rows. The top left corner is a1 and the bottom right corner is g9.
Use '!{0} press 1' to press a button. Use '!{0} words' to get the words in the chat. The order of the buttons is top, right, bottom, and then left.
To press small top buttons, use !{0} L(left), M(middle), R(right). To press bottom buttons use !{0} T(top), B(bottom)
Press the button by name with !{0} press "this". Press the button in column 2 row 3 with !{0} press 2 3. Press the right submit button with !{0} submit right.
!{0} mute [mutes all strings and resets all frets] | !{0} play x 0 0 1 0 2 [play a chord; x means muted; 0 means no fret; otherwise, frets are numbered from 1]
!{0} connect 1 3;3 9;9 7 [Connects the specified points (in this example they make a backwards C), points are in reading order 1-9] | !{0} colorblind [Enables colorblind mode]

Use !{0} order to press the order button, and !{0} submit to press submit. You can do !{0} press mayo bun tomato cheese lettuce onions pickles mustard ketchup meat to press buttons. The timer is enabled on Twitch Plays.
Activate the module using !{0} activate , Submit the correct answer using ! {0} submit ######## .
!{0} submit 1101001010 (Sets the binary to 1101001010, then submits.)
use '!{0} 123456' to press the butterflies in reading order.
Use !{0} press 1 2 3 4 or !{0} 1 2 3 4 to press the buttons 1 2 3 4 in reading order.  You can do !{0} reset to reset.

Tap the buttons with !{0} tap 1 3. Move to the next panel !{0} down. Move to the previous panel with !{0} up. Cycle the panels done so far with !{0} cycle.  Hold the button with !{0} hold 2. Release the button with !{0} release 7.  Buttons are 1, 2, and 3. If the only thing you need to do on the current panel are taps, you can tap and move to the next panel with !{0} tap 1 2 down.
To turn the dial a specific number of times, do "!{0} turn/rotate #". The dial turns # % 4 times based on the command inputted. (4n turns will turn the dial 4 times.)
Enter the correct cipher text with “!{0} press K B Q I S”.
!{0} QWERTYUI [Inputs letters] | !{0} cancel [Deletes inputs]
!{0} submit <num> [Submits the answer with the coefficient of <num>] | Valid answers range from -9 to 9

Use '!{0} holiday' to locate the circled holiday. Use '!{0} left' or '!{0} right' to cycle left or right one month at a time. Use '!{0} press #' to press a certain day. Use '!{0} [month name]' to cycle to the selected month. Use !{0} colorblind to enable colorblind mode.
Press a panel at a specific digit using !{0} panel 2 at 8. Panels are in english reading order. Submit a number using !{0} submit 480.
Use !{0} X to submit a specific letter.
Use !{0} # to select the corresponding chalice.
Use !{0} submit [word] to submit a word. Words containing anything other than letters are ignored.
!{0} press 1234 [Presses the buttons 1, 2, 3 and 4 in this order] | !{0} tap [Taps the display to try to make it work again.]
Submit A4 with “!{0} submit A4”, cycle through the numbers and letters with “!{0} cycle”, or just one with “!{0} cycle letters” or “!{0} cycle numbers”.
Cycle the items with !{0} items. Go to a specific item number with !{0} item 3. Get customers to pay the correct amount with !{0} submit. Return the proper change with !{0} submit 3.24.

!{0} hack <index> [Goes to <index> hack], !{0} lcd/screen/display <amount/cycle,c/fullcycle,fc> [Goes forward on a specific hack information, cycle the whole lcd or cycle all 5 hacks], !{0} submit/sub [Submits with nothing to slap the customer], !{0} submit/sub <change> [Submits the answer into the module], !{0} stabilize/stbl <#/##> [Presses 'Stabilize' depending on what is needed], !{0} patch <None/#> [Press 'Patch' depending on what is needed]

!{0} birds [Cycles through all the birds] | !{0} bird <#> [Goes to the specified bird] | !{0} press <button> [Presses the specified button] | !{0} mash [Mashes the submit button] | Valid buttons are submit, clear, and 1-8 representing the value buttons in reading order
Cycle the positions with !{0} cycle. Submit the safe spot with !{0} press C2.
!{0} press 1 2 3 <s/sub/submit> [Presses the buttons on the bottom in order from left to right and then presses the top one] | !{0} drown [Holds down the top button and releases it after a second]

!{0} press <button> [Presses the specified button] | !{0} press <button> <button> [Example of button chaining] | !{0} reset [Resets all inputs] | Valid buttons are tl, tr, bl, br OR 1-4 being the buttons from in reading order
Use !{0} submit <#> / reset.
Use '!{0} cycle year/zodiac' to cycle the year or or zodiac and e.g. '!{0} submit 1804 wood rat' to sumbit an answer.
!{0} submit <note> <type> [submit a chord] | b and # can be used for flat and sharp. | Types: major, minor and diminished
Submit a chord using !{0} submit A B C# D
Use '!{0} tilt <rotation>' to to rotate the module. For ex. '!{0} tilt up' To press the clock use '!{0} <hour>'! For ex. '!{0} 5'
!{0} submit <word> [Submits the card with the specified word] | !{0} colorblind [Toggles colorblind mode]
To submit the correct answer, type !{0} right / left in chat.

!{0} next [next customer] | !{0} name <name> [select name] | !{0} name <name> (pause) [pause on the name for (pause) seconds, then select] | !{0} sugar/time/stress/size/name [repeat info] | !{0} milk/cream/sprinkles/gluten [toggle a quirk] | !{0} submit <coffee> [partial names are fine]

!{0} submit <colo(u)r> [Submits the specified colo(u)r] | Valid colo(u)r's are Standard, Red, Orange, Yellow, Chartreuse, Lime, Green, Cyan, Blue, Violet, Magenta, Pink, Brown, White, Gray, Black, or Clear
Use !press 1 2 3 the press the buttons from left to right!
!{0} 5 [press the 5th LED in reading order] | !{0} colorblind [enable color-blind mode]
Commands are “col1/.../col6/row1/.../row6” or “c1/.../c6/r1/.../r6”. These can be chained, for example: “!{0} row1 r2 col3 c4”

Submit a color using "!{0} press bigred 1,smallred 2,biggreen 1,smallblue 1" !{0} press <buttonname> <amount of times to push>. If you want to be silly, you can have this module change the color of the status light when solved with "!{0} press smallblue UseRedOnSolve" or UseOffOnSolve. You can make this module tell a story with !{0} tellmeastory, make a needy sound with !{0} needystart or !{0} needyend, fake strike with !{0} faksestrike, and troll with !{0} troll
Type '!{0} press red', '!{0} press r', '!{0} red' or '!{0} r' to press red

Set the answer to red, green, blue, purple with “!{0} set r,g,b,p”. For color, use the first letter of the color, for example, R for red. Exceptions are A for gray and K for black. Submit the answer with “!{0} submit”.
!{0} press # [Presses the button labelled with the number '#'] | !{0} colorblind [Toggles colorblind mode]
Press a button with !{0} <Colour>, // Valid Colours are: Red, Orange, Yellow, Green, Blue, Cyan, Purple, Magenta, Brown, Tan, Grey, Black.
Type '!{0} press top left', '!{0} press tl', '!{0} top left' or '!{0} tl' to press the button in that position. Can also use numbers 1-4 instead (buttons are ordered TL, TR, BL, BR).
!{0} A1 A2 A3 B3 [specify column as letter, then row as number] | !{0} colorblind
Toggle switches with “!{0} 1 2 3 4”. (Optional “toggle/switch/flip/press” command allowed.) Use “!{0} colorblind” to show the colors of the switches.
!{0} set B9 M7 R1 sets the 1st, 2nd, and 3rd dials to Blue 9, Magenta 7, Red 1, !{0} submit 5 presses the submit button when the countdown timer's last digit is a 5.
!{0} press A1 B3 C5... (column [A to G] and row [1 to 5] to press)

!{0} press 1 2 3... (buttons to be pressed [within the range 1-20]) | !{0} show all/top/bottom / 1 2 3... (displays the buttons' info on the screen [all/top/bottom show the respective half of buttons] [numbers are within the range 1-20] [only works with colorblind mode enabled]) | !{0} colorblind/cb (enables colorblind mode)

Submit your answer with “!{0} press 1|R|Y|9|P|0s0|3 (add sX [where 'X' is a digit] to press the button when the last seconds digit of the bomb is 'X')”. Delete screen with “!{0} delete 5 (number of times to press the button)”. Submit answer with “!{0} go 40 (submit when the seconds of the bomb is the number)”. Cancel submitting the answer with “!{0} go cancel/c/stop (stop submitting the answer)”.
